'''蟄伏'''(英文：Torpor)是動物體內生理活動降低的一種狀態，通常是由於[[體溫|體溫]]和[[代謝率|代謝率]]降低而引起的。蟄伏使動物能夠在食物供應匱乏的時期生存下去。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Vuarin |first1=Pauline |last2=Dammhahn |first2=Melanie |last3=Kappeler |first3=Peter M. |last4=Henry |first4=Pierre-Yves |title=When to initiate torpor use? Food availability times the transition to winter phenotype in a tropical heterotherm |journal=Oecologia |date=September 2015 |volume=179 |issue=1 |pages=43–53 |doi=10.1007/s00442-015-3328-0 |pmid=25953115 |bibcode=2015Oecol.179...43V |s2cid=17050304 }}</ref>術語“蟄伏”可以指休眠者在低體溫和代謝率下度過的時間，持續數天至數週，或者少於24小時的時間。

每天進行蟄伏的動物包括[[鳥類|鳥類]]（甚至是微小的[[蜂鳥|蜂鳥]]，尤其是[[夜鳥類|夜鳥類]]）<ref name="Hainsworth(1970)a">{{cite journal |last1=Hainsworth |first1=F. R. |last2=Wolf |first2=L. L. |title=Regulation of Oxygen Consumption and Body Temperature during Torpor in a Hummingbird, Eulampis jugularls |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_science_1970-04-17_168_3929/page/368 |journal=Science |date=17 April 1970 |volume=168 |issue=3929 |pages=368–369 |doi=10.1126/science.168.3929.368 |pmid=5435893 |bibcode=1970Sci...168..368R |s2cid=30793291 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://nationalzoo.si.edu/conservationandscience/migratorybirds/webcam/hummingbirds.cfm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080214224153/http://nationalzoo.si.edu/conservationandscience/migratorybirds/webcam/hummingbirds.cfm |archive-date=2008-02-14 |publisher=Migratory Bird Center, Smithsonian National Zoological Park |title=Hummingbirds |access-date=2021-03-13 |dead-url=no }}</ref>和一些[[哺乳動物|哺乳動物]]，包括許多[[有袋動物|有袋動物]]<ref name="Geiser(1994)a">{{cite journal |last1=Geiser |first1=F |title=Hibernation and Daily Torpor in Marsupials - a Review |journal=Australian Journal of Zoology |date=1994 |volume=42 |issue=1 |page=1 |doi=10.1071/zo9940001 }}</ref><ref name="Stannard2015">{{cite journal |last1=Stannard |first1=H.J. |last2=Fabian |first2=M. |last3=Old |first3=J.M. |title=To bask or not to bask: Behavioural thermoregulation in two species of dasyurid, ''Phascogale calura'' and ''Antechinomys laniger'' |journal=Journal of Thermal Biology |date=2015 |volume=53 |page=66-71 |doi=10.1016/j.jtherbio.2015.08.012| PMID=26590457 }}</ref>、[[囓齒動物|囓齒動物]]（例如[[小鼠|小鼠]]）和[[蝙蝠|蝙蝠]]。<ref name="Bartels(1998)a">{{cite journal |last1=Bartels |first1=W. |last2=Law |first2=B. S. |last3=Geiser |first3=F. |title=Daily torpor and energetics in a tropical mammal, the northern blossom-bat Macroglossus minimus (Megachiroptera) |journal=Journal of Comparative Physiology B: Biochemical, Systemic, and Environmental Physiology |date=7 April 1998 |volume=168 |issue=3 |pages=233–239 |doi=10.1007/s003600050141 |pmid=9591364 |s2cid=16870476 }}</ref>這些動物在白天活動期間保持正常的體溫和活動量，但是在一天的某一期間（通常是夜晚）中，它們的代謝率和體溫下降，以節省能量。

一些動物會季節性地長時間處於不活動的休眠狀態，此時它們的體溫和新陳代謝會降低，而這是由多次蟄伏所造成的。如果發生在[[冬季|冬季]]，則稱為[[冬眠|冬眠]]；如果發生在[[夏季|夏季]]，則稱為[[夏眠|夏眠]]。

蟄伏是一個控制良好的溫度調節過程，而不是像以前認為的那樣，是關閉溫度調節的結果。<ref name="Geiser(2004)a">{{cite journal |last1=Geiser |first1=Fritz |title=Metabolic Rate and Body Temperature Reduction During Hibernation and Daily Torpor |journal=Annual Review of Physiology |date=March 2004 |volume=66 |issue=1 |pages=239–274 |doi=10.1146/annurev.physiol.66.032102.115105 |pmid=14977403 |s2cid=22397415 }}</ref>[[有袋動物|有袋動物]]的蟄伏與非有袋動物的[[哺乳動物|哺乳動物]]（[[真獸下綱|真獸下綱]]）的蟄伏不同。真獸下綱依靠喚醒可以產生熱量的[[棕色脂肪|棕色脂肪]]組織作為加速變暖的機制。有袋動物喚醒的機制尚不清楚，但似乎不依賴棕色脂肪組織。<ref>{{cite book |last1=Dawson |first1=T. J. |last2=Finch |first2=E. |last3=Freedman |first3=L. |last4=Hume |first4=I. D. |last5=Renfree |first5=Marilyn |last6=Temple-Smith |first6=P. D. |chapter=Morphology and Physiology of the Metatheria |chapter-url=https://www.environment.gov.au/system/files/pages/a117ced5-9a94-4586-afdb-1f333618e1e3/files/17-ind.pdf |editor1-last=Walton |editor1-first=D. W. |editor2-last=Richardson |editor2-first=B. J. |title=Fauna of Australia - Volume 1B Mammalia |isbn=978-0-644-06056-1 |access-date=2021-03-13 |archive-date=2021-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210405063215/https://www.environment.gov.au/system/files/pages/a117ced5-9a94-4586-afdb-1f333618e1e3/files/17-ind.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>

